				=09
					<div id=3D"mw-content-text" class=3D"mw-body-content"><div class=3D"mw=
-content-ltr mw-parser-output" lang=3D"en" dir=3D"ltr"><div class=3D"shortd=
escription nomobile noexcerpt noprint searchaux" style=3D"display:none">Ter=
m in statistical hypothesis testing</div>
<p>In <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frequentist" class=3D"mw-red=
irect" title=3D"Frequentist">frequentist</a> <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Statistics" title=3D"Statistics">statistics</a>, <b>power</b> is=
 the probability of detecting an effect (i.e. rejecting the null hypothesis=
) given that some prespecified effect actually exists using a given test in=
 a given context. In typical use, it is a function of the specific test tha=
t is used (including the choice of test statistic and <a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Significance_level" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Sign=
ificance level">significance level</a>), the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Sample_size" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Sample size">sample =
size</a> (more data tends to provide more power), and the <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Effect_size" title=3D"Effect size">effect size</a> =
(effects or correlations that are large relative to the variability of the =
data tend to provide more power).
</p><p>More formally, in the case of a simple <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Hypothesis_test" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Hypothesis test=
">hypothesis test</a> with two hypotheses, the <b>power of the test</b> is =
the probability that the test correctly rejects the <a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Null_hypothesis" title=3D"Null hypothesis">null hypothesi=
s</a> (<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><=
math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle=
 H_{0}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msub>
          <mi>H</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mn>0</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle H_{0}}</annot=
ation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/43910602a221b7a4c373791f94793e3008622070" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.671ex; width:2.985ex; height:2.509ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle H_{=
0}}"></span>) when the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alternative=
_hypothesis" title=3D"Alternative hypothesis">alternative hypothesis</a> (<=
span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xml=
ns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle H_{1}}"=
>
  <semantics>
